[7m                     MINTIA Operating System: Online Manual                    [m

NAME
    login -- console log-in

SYNOPSIS
    login

DESCRIPTION
    login is the program which receives and handles console logins. It is
    invoked by (0)launchtty to manage logins for a given terminal. It should not
    be invoked directly.

    Public user information is stored in two files:

  * /mintia/groups.cfg    Stores group name information.
  * /mintia/users.cfg     Stores user name, preferences, and quota information.

    Private user information is stored in one file:

  * /mintia/login.cfg     Stores password hashes and is only accessible by the
                          root user.

SEE ALSO
    (0)SystemInit
    (0)launchtty
